channel.title: CVE Feed for Bosch -- PRA-ES8P2S
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Bosch -- PRA-ES8P2S

item.title: CVE-2022-32535|2024-08-03T07:46:43.473Z -- bosch -- pra-es8p2s
item.description: The Bosch Ethernet switch PRA-ES8P2S with software version 1.01.05 runs its web server with root privilege. In combination with CVE-2022-23534 this could give an attacker root access to the switch.

item.title: CVE-2022-32534|2024-08-03T07:46:43.351Z -- bosch -- pra-es8p2s
item.description: The Bosch Ethernet switch PRA-ES8P2S with software version 1.01.05 and earlier was found to be vulnerable to command injection through its diagnostics web interface. This allows execution of shell commands.

item.title: CVE-2022-32536|2024-08-03T07:46:43.564Z -- bosch -- pra-es8p2s
item.description: The user access rights validation in the web server of the Bosch Ethernet switch PRA-ES8P2S with software version 1.01.05 was insufficient. This would allow a non-administrator user to obtain administrator user access rights.
